{{Infobox protected area | name = Asessippi Provincial Park | alt_name = | iucn_category = III | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Manitoba | map_width = 200 | map_alt = | map_caption = | relief = | label = | label_position = | mark = | marker_size = | location = Manitoba, Canada | nearest_town = Inglis, Manitoba | coordinates = {{coord|50|57|59|N|101|22|47|W|display=inline,title|region:CA-MB_type:landmark_scale:100000}} | coords_ref = <ref name="GABCJ">{{cite web|title=Asessippi Provincial Park|url=http://www4.rncan.gc.ca/search-place-names/unique/GABCJ|website=Geographical Place Names|publisher=Natural Resources Canada|accessdate=5 July 2017}}</ref> | area_km2 = 23.2 | designation = | authorized = | created = | designated = | established = 1964 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = Government of Manitoba | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = | url = | child = | embedded = }} [[File:Asessippi.JPG|left|200px|Assessippi Ski Resort]] '''Asessippi Provincial Park''' was designated a [[provincial park]] by the Government of Manitoba on April 9, 1964.<ref name="PPS-GOM">{{cite web|title=Asessippi Provincial Park|url=https://www.gov.mb.ca/sd/parks/popular_parks/western/asessippi_info.html|website=Find Your Favourite Park|publisher=Parks and Protected Spaces Branch, Government of Manitoba|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref> It is located in the [[Rural Municipality of Riding Mountain West]], near [[Inglis, Manitoba]], [[Canada]] about 100&nbsp;km west of [[Dauphin, Manitoba|Dauphin]]. The Park is 23.2&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> (9 sq mi).<ref name="PPS-GOM" /> The park is considered to be a [[IUCN protected area categories#Category III — Natural Monument or Feature|Class III protected area]] under the IUCN protected area management categories.<ref>{{cite web|title=Asessippi Provincial Park|url=https://www.protectedplanet.net/asessippi-provincial-park-provincial-park|website=Protected Planet|publisher=UN Environment World Conservation Monitoring Centre|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref>
The focal point is the [[Lake of the Prairies]] also known as [[Shellmouth Reservoir]]. The lake has one of the largest walleye fisheries in Manitoba. The Park includes a large campground with over 100 mostly serviced sites. [[Image:Shellmouth.jpg|thumb|250px|Shellmouth Dam in Asessippi Provincial Park.]] Asessippi Ski Resort is in the area.
