==First WDC/PDC rankings== Following the [[Professional Darts Corporation|World Darts Council]] (now PDC) split from the [[British Darts Organisation]] during 1992-94 the WDC drew up its first ranking list in the run-up to its inaugural [[1994 PDC World Darts Championship|1994 World Championship]]. [[Mike Gregory (darts player)|Mike Gregory]] and [[Chris Johns (darts player)|Chris Johns]] later went back to the BDO set up and [[Bobby George]] and many of the non-UK players never competed in the early days of the WDC.{{citation needed|date=August 2010}}
